REDIS LIST EXPLANATION

POST /goal arrives
        ↓
Redis Queue (score_updates LIST):
  ├─ Stores JSON message temporarily
  ├─ {"matchId":1,"score_home":2,"score_away":0,"timestamp":...}
  └─ Message sits here until consumed
        ↓
Worker BRPOP (polling queue):
  ├─ Detects message
  ├─ Extracts data from JSON
  └─ Removes message from queue
        ↓
Database UPDATE:
  ├─ Execute: UPDATE matches SET score_home=2, score_away=0 WHERE id=1
  └─ Database now synced with cache
        ↓
Redis list becomes empty (message deleted)


Redis Data Types in Your System:

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  STRING: match:1                            │
│  ├─ Created by: GET endpoint (reads DB)     │
│  │  or POST endpoint (updates score)        │
│  ├─ Lifetime: 30 seconds (CACHE_TTL)        │
│  ├─ Auto-deleted: YES                       │
│  └─ Data: Full match object                 │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  LIST: score_updates                        │
│  ├─ Created by: POST endpoint (queuing)     │
│  ├─ Elements added by: LPUSH                │
│  ├─ Elements removed by: BRPOP (worker)     │
│  ├─ Auto-deleted: NO                        │
│  ├─ Manual cleanup: When messages consumed  │
│  └─ Data: JSON messages                     │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘